======================================================================================================================================
																CREATING VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT
======================================================================================================================================

We can create the virtual environment by using 2 modules.
1. venv
2. virtualenv


What is the difference venv and virtualenv?
===========================================
venv 		==> this module comes built-in with python installation.
virtualenv  ==> this module need to be installed explicitly.


how to decide that, which module to be used for creating virtual environment?
==============================================================================
scenarion-1: when we want to create an virtual environment with a specific python version other than the default/global version, then we have
to use "virtualenv" module.

scenarion-2: when we want to create an virtual environment with default/global python version, then we have to use "venv" module.



Creating virtual environment by using "virtualenv" module?
===========================================================
	installing the module
		> pip install virtualenv
	
	creating the virtual environment
		> python -m virtualenv -p <"specific python version installed path"> <virtual-environment-name>
	
		Ex:
		> python -m virtualenv -p "C:\Users\Vissu\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python310\python.exe" PyLatestVer
		

Creating virtual environment by using "venv" module?
=====================================================
	Creating the virtual environment
		> python -m venv <virtual-environment-name>
		
		Ex:
		> python -m venv PyLatestVer-1
